data.title: Inventor from Houston develops Tumbler Frying Machine to rotate food items for even frying.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 30, 2025, an inventor from Houston, Texas shared his creation, the TUMBLER FRYING MACHINE/ ROTATING FRYER. The innovative machine automatically rotates food items as they fry to ensure even frying. This inventive solution aims to improve the quality of fried foods by ensuring consistent cooking. The inventor highlighted the importance of this design feature in achieving evenly fried food items.

data.title: China's rare earth export denial to defense firms predates recent escalation. Trump-Xi truce sparks rare earth stocks dip.
data.description: China has been refusing to export rare earth materials to defense companies, even prior to the recent escalation in tension. Following the trade truce between Trump and Xi, uncertainties persist regarding this issue. As a result, stocks related to rare earth minerals have witnessed a decline.

data.title: Chewy to acquire SmartEquine from Covetrus, allowing Covetrus to focus on core business. Announcement made on Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: Covetrus, a leading animal-health technology and services company, has disclosed a recent transaction focusing on their core business of providing technology solutions for veterinarians. The transaction took place on October 30, 2025 in Portland, Maine. This move allows Covetrus to enhance their primary business function.

data.title: Teamsters at Zenith Logistics in Cincinnati ratify new contract, including pay increase and improved benefits.
data.description: Workers belonging to Local Union 100 have secured a significant pay raise, comprehensive health benefits through Teamsters, and better working conditions. The members, employed at Zenith Logistics which serves Kroger, approved a new collective bargaining agreement for six years.

data.title: SPX FLOW offers support for customers with new maintenance, spares, and service agreements for 2026. #manufacturing #SPXFLOW
data.description: In Charlotte, North Carolina on October 30, 2025, SPX FLOW is aiding customers worldwide in gearing up for 2026 by offering innovative proactive maintenance, quick-ship spare parts, and customized service contracts to ensure optimal performance of essential equipment. As the year 2025 comes to a close, manufacturers and producers are benefiting from these initiatives.

data.title: Black-Owned The Old G gin wins "Best Gin in Show" at Global Spirit Awards. Introduces new 200ml bottle. Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: Following the recent release of a 200ml pocket bottle, The Old G, a London Dry gin brand that is Black- and minority-owned, has received an award in Las Vegas on October 30, 2025. This recognition comes at a time when the brand is expanding its cultural impact and experiencing rapid growth, even in the face of industry challenges.

data.title: FXCubic's FXCubic Bridge processed record 3,000 yards in trading volume in Sep 2025, Company milestone reached.
data.description: In London on October 30, 2025, FXCubic, a top player in liquidity aggregation and risk management technology, revealed that its primary product, the FXCubic Bridge, handled more than 3,000 yards in trading volume in September 2025. This achievement represents a significant milestone for the company.

data.title: Recreatives Industries (OTC: RECX) halves authorized shares from 1.45B to 700M to boost shareholder value.
data.description: Recreatives Industries (OTC: RECX) has reduced its authorized shares from 1.45 billion to 700 million. This move is aimed at strengthening disciplined equity management and enhancing shareholder value.

data.title: VinFast's VF 8 bridges Vietnam and Canada's EV differences. 100k+ vehicles delivered in Vietnam.
data.description: VinFast's VF 8 model is symbolizing the connection between different approaches to electrification as Vietnam rapidly progresses and Canada steadily shifts in that direction. This electric vehicle is showcasing the boldness of a new player in the market alongside the cautiousness of a nation adapting to electric transportation. While global interest in electric vehicles has been varied, with some markets experiencing a decline, Vietnam is experiencing an increase. VinFast, Vietnam's domestic automaker, has successfully distributed over 100,000 vehicles.

data.title: MeaningSphere launches new digital learning experiences for U.S. workers to find more fulfilling work. Media release on Oct. 30, 2025.
data.description: A new curated collection of digital learning experiences has been launched, offering easy access and self-paced learning to individuals. This initiative aims to empower people to shape a fulfilling work life that aligns with their aspirations. The program was introduced in Horsham, Pennsylvania on October 30, 2025. This career-focused personal development company aims to revolutionize the way individuals approach professional growth with its innovative platform.

data.title: Iovate Health Sciences forms new scientific advisory board at SupplySide 2025 to advance muscle health with digital education series.
data.description: A new digital education series has been launched by Iovate Health Sciences International Inc., a leading company in performance nutrition and wellness solutions, as part of the Advisory board Commences at SupplySide 2025 event taking place in Toronto on Oct. 30, 2025. The series aims to provide valuable insights and information.

data.title: Suriname extends offer to tender for cash its 7.95% Cash/PIK Securities due 2033, dated Oct 23, 2025.
data.description: The Republic of Suriname in Paramaribo revealed an extension of its invitation on October 30, 2025, initially dated October 23, 2025. This invitation calls for each holder to submit offers to tender for cash the 7.95% Cash/PIK.

data.title: Aya Gold & Silver sponsors 1st Canadian-Moroccan team in 2026 Rallye Aïcha Des Gazelles. Key figures: Asmaa Hammoudi, Benoit La Salle, Mustapha El Ouafi, Zineb Hammoudi.
data.description: Image 1 shows Asmaa Hammoudi and Benoit La Salle, CEO and President of Aya Gold & Silver. Image 2 features Mustapha El Ouafi, President and Managing Director of Aya Gold & Silver in Morocco, alongside Zineb Hammoudi.

data.title: Northern Horizon Capital AS shares sold by Northern Horizon A/S to Antanas Anskaitis, Antanas Danys, and Tomas Milašauskas.
